**Default Function: They are of two types:-
1.CONSTRUCTOR-> It does not need any datatype & does not return any value.
             -> It is automatically called/invoked once into a program.
             ->***when an object is created constructor is automatically called.//1 constructor for 1 object.
             -> 3 types of Constructor:-
                  -> Default constructor: does not have any parameter.
                  -> Parameterised Constructor: have atleast 1 parameter.
                  -> Copy Constructor : Object as a parameter.

2.DESTRUCTOR-> It is the last function which is invoked/automatically called when an object is destroyed/delete.

***Default Function has same as class name.

                                        ***DEFAULT CONSTRUCTOR IN CPP CODE:


#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

class Student{
public:
    string name;
    int roll_no;
    int age;
//default constructor

    void study(){
        cout<<"default constructor called"<<endl;
    }
};

int main(){
    Student obj;
    //dot operator: access methods and properties of a class
    obj.name ="Naman";
    obj.age  =22;
    obj.study();
}


                                                            ***PARAMETERISED CONSTRUCTOR IN CPP


#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

class Student{
public:
    string name;
    int roll_no;
    int age;
// parameterised constructor

Student(int a ){
    age=a;
    cout<<age<<endl;
}
};

int main(){
    Student obj(22);
    //dot operator: access methods and properties of a class
    obj.name ="Naman";
    obj.age  =22;
   return 0;
}


